qas.question: Visits to The Times website have decreased by how much since October 2011?
What is the reason for the dramatic drop in visits to The Times website?
In April 2009, how many readers did the timesonline website have per day?
As of October 2011, how many subscribers does The Times' digital product currently have?

context: Visits to the websites have decreased by <a0_0>87%<a0_0/> since the <a1_0>paywall<a1_0/> was introduced, from 21 million unique users per month to 2.7 million. In April 2009, the timesonline site had a readership of <a2_0>750,000<a2_0/> readers per day. As of October 2011, there were around <a3_0>111,000<a3_0/> subscribers to The Times' digital products.
